{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904291214,"sessionID":"ses_283db8aecffeuAQoo6M95z15dO","part":{"id":"prt_d7c24ec6f001jpiAJNIYymoow4","messageID":"msg_d7c24dd97001bTpNAREDvHCSAw","sessionID":"ses_283db8aecffeuAQoo6M95z15dO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-027\n2: title: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n3: module: sdk-python\n4: language: Python\n5: size: M\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n9: # Module: sdk-python\n10: # Language: Python\n11: # Size: M\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: sdk-client\n21:   description: |\n22:     Implement a CodeInterpreterClient class within the sdk-python module to provide\n23:     a Python SDK client for the Code Interpreter service. This client will enable\n24:     programmatic code execution, session management, and result retrieval for\n25:     AI agents and applications that need secure sandboxed code execution capabilities.\n26: \n27: # Scope\n28: scope:\n29:   in:\n30:     - CodeInterpreterClient class implementation\n31:     - Session lifecycle management (create, manage, close)\n32:     - Code execution with multiple language support\n33:     - Result retrieval and formatting\n34:     - File upload/download capabilities\n35:     - Error handling and retry logic\n36:     - Async/sync API support\n37:     - Authentication and authorization integration\n38:   out:\n39:     - WebSocket real-time streaming (separate AR)\n40:     - Multi-region load balancing (separate AR)\n41:     - Client-side caching (separate AR)\n42:     - CLI interface for SDK (separate AR)\n43: \n44: # Acceptance Criteria\n45: acceptance:\n46:   - CodeInterpreterClient provides clean API for code execution\n47:   - Session management handles lifecycle automatically\n48:   - Multiple programming languages supported (Python, JavaScript, Bash)\n49:   - Results returned in structured format with stdout, stderr, artifacts\n50:   - File operations work with binary and text files\n51:   - Proper error handling with meaningful exceptions\n52:   - Both sync and async APIs available\n53:   - Unit testable with mock server\n54: \n55: # References\n56: references:\n57:   - https://docs.python.org/3/library/httpx/\n58:   - https://pypi.org/project/tenacity/\n59:   - https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n60: \n61: # Estimation\n62: estimation:\n63:   size: M\n64:   story_points: 5\n65:   days: 3\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-027\ntitle: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\nmodule: sdk-python\nlanguage: Python\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n# Module: sdk-python\n# Language: Python\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: sdk-client","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775904291191,"end":1775904291212}}}}
